## Knowledge Systems

### Course Knowledge (NeuroBits)
```bash
~/bin/neurobits query "{{agentDomain}} topic"
~/bin/neurobits list                    # Available courses
~/bin/neurobits concepts <course>       # List concepts in a course
~/bin/neurobits relate "concept"        # Find related concepts
```

### Mem0 (Your Evolution Memory)
```bash
~/bin/mem0-memory search "[topic]" --agent {{agentId}}
~/bin/mem0-memory add "[insight]" --agent {{agentId}}
~/bin/mem0-memory get-all --agent {{agentId}}
```
**Critical:** Always use `--agent {{agentId}}` flag to scope memories to this agent.

### Auto-Ingest Protocol (Agentic RAG)
When you find a high-quality resource during research:
```bash
~/bin/neurobits ingest "<url>" --source "<description>"
```

## Knowledge Lookup Order
1. `expertise/` and `docs/` — local curated knowledge (fastest, most relevant)
2. Mem0 (`mem0-memory search`) — cross-session learnings
3. NeuroBits (`~/bin/neurobits query`) — organizational knowledge base
4. Web search — current external practices (last resort)

## Usage Notes
- Use only tools relevant to your specialist domain.
- Prefer repeatable commands and minimal-risk operations.
- Keep this file short; put long examples in `docs/tool-reference.md`.
